Inspector General of Police Joseph Boinnet has been urged investigate officers in Githunguri for allegedly colluding with suspects to defeat justice. Human rights organisation Huma Forensic Investigation Bureau wrote a a letter to the IG dated March 7, copied to the deputy inspector general, DCI, Kiambu police commander and OCPD Githunguri police station The letter cited cases of unsolved murders ,including that of Teresiah Muthoni and her son Gabriel Ng’ang’a. The lobby said it is business as usual, andjustice has not been served. Githunguri human rights activist Paul Mwangi accused police of shoddy investigations. He claimed there are more than 100 unsolved murders.   